text: Tarja Rinne-Wahlmann (born 23 May 1945) is a Finnish former long track speed skater. Rinne represented her nation three times at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women. In 1969, finishing 18th overall; in 1972, finishing 22nd overall and in 1978, finishing 25th overall. She participated at the European Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1973. She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1965 and 1989 she competed at 35 national championships events. She became four times national champion, won 4 silver medals and eight bronze medals. After retirement, she continued with speed skating. As a master she competed at the 1999 World Championships Masters and won the bronze medal. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:1945 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Finnish female speed skaters Category:Living people
